The paper discusses the use of behavioural types for the analysis of security properties in distributed systems. This topic is closely related to programming languages (cs.PL) and security and privacy (cs.CR), as well as software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of logic (cs.LO) for the analysis of security properties, which is another possible sub-category.
